<div style="width:750px; height:300px; font-size:15px; float:left; margin:auto; font-weight:bold; font-variant:small-caps;"><h1>Full Truckload (FTS) Services</h1>
One of the primary services offered by trucking companies is Full Truckload transportation. 
This service is best suited for large shipments that require the entire capacity of a truck, typically over 10,000 pounds or occupying more than 12 linear feet of space. 
FTL shipments are often faster than Less-than-Truckload shipments, as they generally travel directly from the point of origin to the destination without additional stops for consolidation or deconsolidation. 
This service is ideal for businesses that need to transport large quantities of goods quickly and efficiently.Full truckload, commonly referred to as FTL, is a type of shipping mode whereby a truck carries one dedicated shipment. In other words, the journey is reserved for one shipment only. FTL trucking has several advantages over the alternative trucking shipment mode, LTL, or less than a full truckload shipment.
For shipments that are large enough to fill or nearly fill an entire shipping container, full truckloads work out cheaper.
Full truckloads are much less encumbered by size and weight restrictions.
